                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2">xxyz</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#0A0634" valign="top"><font color="#FFFFFF" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;04/10/2003&nbsp;: 7:00:17 PM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Here's a little story.<br />I had a really nasty experience here recently. Me and a friend decided to come here (we are both L58) and see if we could bring in some loot. After reading the guides here it sounded like a cinch. Tons of plat, easy places to fear kite in. I had seen a ton of people swear to it. Unfortunately I had NOT heard anything about a mob at zone in seeing through invis in the guides.<br /><br />Well immediately after we both zoned in with Invis on, whorl attacked us. We both FD'd with around 70% health. So here we are, laying here at the zone in with the whorl, a named horse, 3 regular plains steeds, and 2 gale wolfs all in sight. What to do?<br /><br />I decided to be brave and I jumped up and ran to the west wall to get the whorl away from my partner. Two steeds running fast as hell jumped me and I got FD off with 15% health.<br />I told my partner it was safe, so he got up.<br />A gale wolf was near him and it aggroed. He ran off to the west wall near me and FD failed on him, there goes a corpse.<br />Obviously he was pretty upset, since there is NO ZONE OUT from this place and a 150pt or so quadding mob right at zone in that sees through invis.<br />I was safe, but pretty low on health. I FD'd a few more times to try and clear aggro when the coast was clear, and then gated out.<br /><br />So my partner has his corpse stuck in this place with a whorl that is seeing through invis RIGHT at zone in. Being the considerate person I am and feeling bad for the guy, and feeling kind of guilty since it was my idea to go here in the first place, I bought an essence emerald in bazaar for 450pp of my own money (ouch) and proceeded to take the long walk back to PoG. <br />Zoned in again, *this* time with manaskin up.<br />Whorl went right through the whole manaskin before I got an FD off. I took a look around, and there were mobs everywhere. Wolves and Steeds. I decided to make a run for the west wall, and FD, while dragging his corpse behind.<br />What other choices could I have?<br />It worked the first time right? And I had manaskin up this time. Easy.<br />Well, I stood up, and started running. Almost IMMEDIATELY I saw a flash of fire and knew I was in deep ****. Right when I was about ready to FD up on the hill, or hit harmshield, *BAM* another nuke, but this time it stunned me.<br />I watched helplessly while the whorl, a couple steeds, and a gale wolf proceeded to pound my helpless ass into the earthen plains.<br />So here I am, back at PoK, with some 9% of my level lost, and 450pp blown on an EE that would never get used.<br />Both of us are guildless, and we play on Kane Bayle, usually the MOST underpopulated server.<br />What are the options?<br />No guilds ever raid PoG on my server.<br />I don't know enough people of high level to scrounge a raid together.<br />There is no way in hell we can get back in there without having our butts handed to us with the whorl at zone in, and neither of us want to risk losing another 10% of our level trying.<br /><br />Just then I was almost prepared to quit EQ in frustration. The recent nerf to charm making it nearly impossible to use to get quick AAs did not help my mood much.<br /><br />Surely there was no way I could get my stuff back. But, before hitting the Delete button, I decided to just forget about it all, and get some sleep. I was really tired and pretty fed up with the events of the night.<br /><br />Next morning, in a last ditch effort, which I was sure WOULDN'T work (since I had heard horror stories of other people unable to reach their corpse and having it rot in the 7 days), I petitioned that I needed help getting my corpse back because it was in a really nasty situation.<br />Waited 2 hours.<br />GM Kallius tells you: Greetings, fellow citizen of Norrath. I understand your problem, yadda yadda. I can not summon your corpse across zones but I can drag it for you from the zone in.<br /><br />Well, that's a lot of help. Now I can zone in and die again with the comforting knowledge that my corpse is even farther away from me.<br /><br />You tell GM Kallius: Can you remove the whorl from zone in, there is no way I can get back in without dying since it sees through invis.<br /><br />GM Kallius tells you: Well, come to the zone in point to PoG and I will see if I can help. Don't take too long.<br /><br />You tell GM Kallius: Uhhh.. Dude, do you know how far PoG is from PoK? I don't even know if I can find a port and the walk will take forever!<br /><br />GM Kallius tells you: Then I guess you had better start moving your booty, aka get those legs walking :)<br /><br />So, to make a long story short.. <br />He had me zone in, whorl was gone, and dragged my corpse for me to the upper wall.<br />Unfortunately the res time had expired on it, but I got all of my items back.<br />And I've noticed my partner has gotten his back too somehow, so all has turned out O.K. Minus the fact that I lost 10% Exp and 450pp all for nothing.<br /><br />Moral of the story? Stay the hell away from here unless you're feeling lucky, have a full group, or know that the whorl isn't going to be seeing invis when you come in. Otherwise this place will start to look a lot like the Plane of Nightmares, literally.</span></font></td>
